    <ns1495:para xmlns:ns1495="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> A component's natural coordinate system.</ns1495:para>
<ns1496:para xmlns:ns1496="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Each Component has initially an integer coordinate system in device units
(<ns1497:abbrev xmlns:ns1497="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i.e.</ns1497:abbrev> pixels). These range from (0, 0) to (width-1, height-1). The origin 
of the device coordinate system is the upper left corner with the 
$x$-coordinate increasing to the west, and the $y$-coordinate increasing 
towards the south.</ns1496:para>
    
